Swagger UICurl <p>Click on the <code>POST</code> endpoint and then on the <code>Try it out</code> button. Fill in the <code>body</code> with the following content and click on the <code>Execute</code> button.</p> <pre><code>{
"_id": "11111111-2222-3333-4444-555555555555"
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>curl -X 'POST' \
'http://localhost:8000/basemongomodel/' \
-H 'accept: application/json' \
-H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
-d '{
"_id": "11111111-2222-3333-4444-555555555555"
}'
</code></pre> <p>The response should be similar to the following:</p> <pre><code>{
  "_id": "11111111-2222-3333-4444-555555555555"
}
</code></pre> <p>Feel free to test and play with the other endpoints as well.</p>
